        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: shard local Swift tests",
        "body": "## Summary\n- route local full-suite test entry points through the existing suite-shard runner\n- preserve CI's one-suite isolation through wrapper environment overrides\n- align active contributor and release docs on `make test`\n\nThe aggregate `swift test` process is not hermetic under this repository's shared AppKit/global-state test load: independent suites pass, while a monolithic run can produce timing-dependent cross-suite failures. Sharding contains that state while retaining the same discovered test coverage.\n\n## Validation\n- `python3 Scripts/ci_swift_test_by_suite.py --group-size 12 --timeout 180` (441 suites passed)\n- `./Scripts/test.sh --limit-groups 1`\n- wrapper invoked from `/tmp` with `--list-only` (441 suites discovered)\n- `make check`\n- `bash -n Scripts/test.sh Scripts/compile_and_run.sh Scripts/prepare_upstream_pr.sh`\n- `git diff --check`\n- local autoreview: clean\n",
